1
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:39,030
[A Love Never Lost]

2
00:01:40,550 --> 00:01:41,890
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,970
He doesn't want to draw?

4
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:51,400
How can you be so straightforward?

5
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:51,759
You'll

6
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:53,310
scare the old man away.

7
00:01:53,430 --> 00:01:54,640
When it comes to such a scary deal,

8
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,640
you will scare even the donkey away

9
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,170
when you tell them about it.

10
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,680
You should know what to do

11
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,280
and treat him with kindness.

12
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:03,070
How could I reason with him?

13
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,470
Not to mention kindness.

14
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:06,880
You should have argued the case for revolution

15
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,810
and expressed the grief of people.

16
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,620
Where did my digest go?

17
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,060
What digest?

18
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,500
It's Brother Zou Rong's new work.

19
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:22,230
Oh yes.

20
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,110
It's here.

21
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:25,260
I'll read a paragraph to you.

22
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,800
Listen to this. Just one paragraph.

23
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:30,000
We should sweep away

24
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:33,870
thousands of years of authoritarianism,

25
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:35,290
shed away

26
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:39,070
thousands of years of slavery,

27
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,310
and wash away

28
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,750
the shame of

29
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:47,600
260 years of cruelty and abuse.

30
00:02:52,829 --> 00:02:56,020
Let's purify mainland China,

31
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:01,800
where the Emperor's descendants can continue to live on prosperously.

32
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,360
Some may have resurrected

33
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:05,570
and returned to their senses.

34
00:03:05,570 --> 00:03:06,850
They got out of the 18 layers of hell,

35
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:08,420
ascended to the 33 levels of heaven

36
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:10,530
and are full of zeal and vigor.

37
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,630
They think they are the best and most unique.

38
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:14,870
A purpose of greatness and excellence

39
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,190
lies in

40
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:17,840
the revolution.

41
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,079
The revolution

42
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:22,000
is lofty.

43
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:24,610
The revolution is exuberant.

44
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:28,880
Where are you?

45
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,900
I got you some water to wash your feet.

46
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,310
Look at you.

47
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:36,750
I am trying to teach you.

48
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:38,120
Do you really think that

49
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,430
everyone could listen to what you have to say?

50
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:41,620
He can’t possibly understand if you never say anything.

51
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:43,130
What do you have to say that he doesn't know about?

52
00:03:43,130 --> 00:03:44,079
He's 73 years old.

53
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,150
He drew 9 cranes

54
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:46,800
for Empress Cixi.

55
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,480
What is it that he hasn't seen?

56
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:49,960
I have something else.

57
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,620
I'll give you a new paragraph.

58
00:03:58,720 --> 00:03:59,960
Mr. Wu?

59
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,240
I'm your neighbor.

60
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:02,870
I brought some boiled meat

61
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,680
for Miss Shuhong.

62
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:06,550
You should try some too.

63
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,130
Thank you, Madam Liang.

64
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:11,350
For these,

65
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:13,960
you need to cut them up into thin slices and dip it in soy sauce.

66
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,220
If you can't finish it,

67
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,870
it's still really delicious with rice.

68
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,570
I will get going.

69
00:04:18,570 --> 00:04:19,529
Let me see you off.

70
00:04:19,529 --> 00:04:20,649
No need. Go back.

71
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:30,180
What a delicacy.

72
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,670
Let's slice two pieces and give it a try.

73
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:44,810
Come in.

74
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:50,650
You are so well-dressed.

75
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:54,740
Where's your mother?

76
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,140
She went to the clinic to see a doctor.

77
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,160
This is your family's plate.

78
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,310
Your mother's boiled meat

79
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,160
is delicious.

80
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,880
What are you holding?

81
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,110
You want to see it?

82
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,930
Then, hold it for me.

83
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,980
Put it on the floor.

84
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,480
Pull.

85
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:40,320
A Chinese painting?

86
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:43,600
Cai Guangqi's Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains.

87
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:44,960
It's really nice.

88
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:48,600
My guardian will definitely love it.

89
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:49,800
Guardian?

90
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Where can I buy a painting like this?

91
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:54,909
It's too expensive.

92
00:05:54,909 --> 00:05:56,770
You don't have to spend the money.

93
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:58,070
Pass it to me.

94
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,720
Hold this end.

95
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,160
Pull it tight.

96
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,360
Why are you

97
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,490
so dressed up today?

98
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,040
Today is my big day.

99
00:06:11,530 --> 00:06:13,310
I just said goodbye to the Inukai Regiment

100
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:15,310
and ended six months of enlistment.

101
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:16,040
Really?

102
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:18,370
Should I congratulate you?

103
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,790
Wouldn't you feel awkward

104
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:25,550
congratulating a member of the imperial clan?

105
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,310
Awkward?

106
00:06:26,330 --> 00:06:27,860
What's so awkward about it?

107
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,480
If I'm not mistaken,

108
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,390
Mr. Wu

109
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:32,720
seems to be

110
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,550
a political refugee from Tokyo.

111
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,780
You have a good eye.

112
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,380
Do I need a good eye to tell?

113
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,040
I don't think

114
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,360
he's all that profound.

115
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,090
He's just an ordinary scholar.

116
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:48,290
You don't have to be wary of me.

117
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,360
In Tokyo,

118
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,670
there are three propositions

119
00:06:50,670 --> 00:06:52,330
for every two Chinese person.

120
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:54,310
Don't talk to me about the revolution.

121
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:55,159
To be honest,

122
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:55,920
I still

123
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,280
don't understand this word.

124
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,400
Isn't it simple?

125
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,710
To put it bluntly,

126
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,710
a revolution is a change of dynasty.

127
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,150
A change of dynasty?

128
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:03,920
Yes.

129
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:06,120
If that's the case,

130
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,270
the Qing dynasty should not be called the Qing dynasty.

131
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:09,510
Then what should we call it?

132
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,600
The Ming dynasty?

133
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,840
You should ask Mr. Wu instead.

134
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:30,270
He didn't see me, right?

135
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,659
So what if he did?

136
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,530
You're right.

137
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,560
I saw that you guys were being polite

138
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,159
and even greeted each other.

139
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:43,120
Well then, what else could we have done instead?

140
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,600
Should we have resorted to arms?

141
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,240
Didn't you come to Japan

142
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,600
just to study military affairs?

143
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,380
Aren't military affairs all about resorting to arms?

144
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:49,180
That's wrong.

145
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:50,720
Modern military affairs

146
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,480
go far beyond physical combat.

147
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,409
The purpose of my studies here

148
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:55,830
can be summarized into eight words.

149
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:58,000
To revitalize our national defense, and to save our country.

150
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:58,950
Oh my god.

151
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,350
Why are all men like this?

152
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,600
Isn't Mr. Wu also...

153
00:08:02,830 --> 00:08:04,000
Are all of you men

154
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,830
willing to be

155
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,360
the father of this country?

156
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,520
In my opinion,

157
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,390
it's still not clear

158
00:08:09,410 --> 00:08:11,190
who is saving who is in this country.

159
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:12,120
Congratulations again

160
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,600
on completing your enlistment.

161
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,150
And thank you for your mother's

162
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:17,080
extremely delicious boiled meat.

163
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:32,789
[Bamboo]

164
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,720
Welcome back.

165
00:08:42,990 --> 00:08:44,250
Duke Ayakura

166
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,950
is too kind.

167
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,510
He came to the clinic himself.

168
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:50,420
I'm kind of embarrassed about it.

169
00:08:50,670 --> 00:08:51,280
Really?

170
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,390
Actually, my sickness

171
00:08:52,390 --> 00:08:54,420
has not acted up even once since I came to Japan.

172
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:55,030
Look.

173
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,060
I ended up with such a huge pile of medicine.

174
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:05,670
The girl next door came by?

175
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,580
You mean Mrs. Wu?

176
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:08,960
Mrs. Wu?

177
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,130
Yes, that Chinese woman next door?

178
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,910
Why does hearing this from you

179
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:16,870
sound so awkward to me?

180
00:09:17,270 --> 00:09:18,000
Awkward?

181
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:18,960
What's awkward?

182
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:21,240
Why haven't I heard that

183
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:21,960
this girl is

184
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,150
Mr. Wu's wife?

185
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:25,450
It doesn't seem like it either.

186
00:09:25,450 --> 00:09:26,850
I've been to their house.

187
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:29,170
They have separate living quarters.

188
00:09:29,170 --> 00:09:30,350
Madam said that

189
00:09:30,810 --> 00:09:32,470
they are teacher and student.

190
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:34,710
Did you really have to get to the bottom of it,

191
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:35,350
Mother?

192
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:37,270
Because I have a son.

193
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:39,550
I think she's a nice girl.

194
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,720
Of course I have to put more effort into it.

195
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,320
Don't you make this about me.

196
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,480
Son,

197
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,960
I think

198
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:47,550
you two

199
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:49,160
look good together.

200
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:53,750
Mother.

201
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,180
Let me tell you.

202
00:09:56,660 --> 00:09:58,590
Among the Chinese people in Tokyo,

203
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,250
9 out of 10 of them

204
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,020
lean towards the revolution.

205
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:05,150
No way.

206
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,390
Think about it.

207
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:07,240
How well

208
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:07,910
has the court governed

209
00:10:07,910 --> 00:10:09,480
the country over the past few years?

210
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,910
If you compare it to the Japanese society,

211
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:11,910
maybe one day,

212
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,040
even your son will become...

213
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,860
How can you say such nonsense?

214
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:29,750
You want a revolution too?

215
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,000
Are you also not satisfied with the court?

216
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,600
Are you also not satisfied with your ancestors?

217
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,720
Bullshit!

218
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:38,210
Listen up, Liang Xiang.

219
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,120
If I hear you

220
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,270
spewing such nonsense again,

221
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:43,120
I'll rip your mouth away.

222
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:45,990
How dare you!

223
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,260
Mother.

224
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,570
I'm just reminding you

225
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,600
not to go around

226
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,600
looking for your daughter-in-law.

227
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:02,720
Firstly,

228
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:05,150
I don't need you to do it.

229
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,670
Secondly,

230
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,080
with your son's ability,

231
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:08,630
I can easily

232
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:10,420
find you a daughter-in-law

233
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:12,110
who can bear many grandchildren for you.

234
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:13,110
Believe it or not.

235
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:16,750
That would be best.

236
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,080
Why are you dressed like this today?

237
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,130
The carp has leaped over the dragon's gate,

238
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:28,790
Mother.

239
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,240
Good boy.

240
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:33,110
You are indeed my son.

241
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:39,940
[Imperial Japanese Army Academy]

242
00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:41,120
Shoot!

243
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,630
Raise the flag.

244
00:11:54,770 --> 00:11:56,010
Salute!

245
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:05,270
Our hard days

246
00:12:05,290 --> 00:12:06,440
is finally over!

247
00:12:06,470 --> 00:12:07,370
We don't have to wash dishes,

248
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:09,630
chop firewood, or feed the pigs anymore!

249
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:11,120
Later, let's go out

250
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,510
for a drink together!

251
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,720
Okay!

252
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:14,970
Don't drink.

253
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,030
Have you forgotten about what happened

254
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:17,030
when you drank the last time?

255
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,150
If you don't want to drink, you can just watch.

256
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,120
Kaizhi, let's drink together.

257
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,120
I'll drink with you.

258
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:20,600
Okay.

259
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,440
Tonight,

260
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,600
let's get drunk.

261
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,240
Okay.

262
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,250
Kaizhi,

263
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,700
why do you look strange in my eyes now?

264
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:30,410
It's only been a few days since I last saw you.

265
00:12:30,410 --> 00:12:31,740
Turn around. Let me see.

266
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,690
Yes, something feels strange.

267
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,520
What's strange?

268
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:41,600
Kaizhi,

269
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:43,050
where is your braid?

270
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:48,190
The braid?

271
00:12:48,380 --> 00:12:49,780
I cut it.

272
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,360
You cut it?

273
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,770
You're not a rebel, are you?

274
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,790
What?

275
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,550
After we finish our enlistment,

276
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:58,340
we'll become a part of the foreign faction.

277
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,480
Why should we keep it?

278
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,630
No one will laugh at us anymore.

279
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:02,760
It's more convenient to sleep as well.

280
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:05,470
Both of them had also cut their braids.

281
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,450
You guys have cut yours too?

282
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:10,490
How dare you cut it?

283
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:11,850
Qianli,

284
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,670
why don’t you

285
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:14,650
cut your braid too?

286
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:15,680
No, I won't.

287
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:16,870
When we return home,

288
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:18,120
how can we face Mr. Yuan if we had cut it?

289
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,200
That's easy.

290
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:20,280
When you head back,

291
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:22,880
isn't it more convenient to just get a fake one?

